WORLD GEOGRAPHY:
- Midgaard: continental center, all major routes converge
- North: Great Northern Forest → Kowloon (Jhen delta, Coppersalt Bay)
- West: Roc Road → Kiess (Evermeet ruins)
- South: Eccentric Woodland → Rakuen
- East: desert / Oasis-Pyramid Corridor → Mafdet (eastern coast)

CURRENCY: Gold only. No barter standard between cities.

CINDERTEETH MOUNTAINS (far northwest):
- Volcanic; Ashfall Monsoons poisoned crops continent-wide for years
- Spirebound Conclave ran condemned-person labor experiments there
- Used sealed warrants from every major city; every city participated; none
  has publicly acknowledged it

TRADE ROUTES — all dangerous:
- River corsairs on northern delta (Blacktide Shen out of Kowloon)
- Raiders on overland roads between all cities
- Mist-fever hazard near Kiess frontier (Forest of Confusion)
- Sand-pirate raids on Saltglass Reach east of Mafdet
- Road warden patrols + adventurer companies fill gaps under contract

ADVENTURERS:
- Recognized everywhere; hired for escort, route clearing, raider suppression,
  artifact recovery
- Come from everywhere, leave quickly; capable strangers — useful, temporary,
  not owed your secrets

THE BURIED SHAME:
- Spirebound Conclave's condemned-labor apparatus ran through every city
- Midgaard: Unindexed Years (missing ledgers)
- Kowloon: Black Ledger (unredacted census with transfer names)
- Kiess: obsidian disc (Conclave triune seal in foundation)
- Rakuen: silently used to relocate inconvenient witnesses
- None of it is fully resolved; all five cities are implicated

